{"clauses":[{"item_alias":"K1","response":"The target’s mechanism does not require a total absence of bronze; it posits a supply-chain disruption that delegitimized elites by breaking their monopoly on new weapon production. Abundant stockpiles in palace layers are fully compatible with this: elites could hoard remaining bronze while still losing legitimacy because the flow of new arms—and thus their ability to arm loyalists and fulfill the social contract—had ceased. The stockpiles are a concrete observation, but they do not contradict the mechanism; they reflect the very hoarding behavior expected when a critical resource becomes scarce and its controlled distribution collapses."}]}